From 99276c3fbbbffbea063372cb65fb6ba554c3cd38 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thom de Hoog <thomdehoog@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 17:22:19 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Add optional external command server (Tools -> Command
 Server...)

mesoSPIM-control has no external control API: everything runs in-process inside
the Qt event loop, so a separate program cannot drive the microscope. This adds
an OPT-IN, OFF-BY-DEFAULT TCP command server that exposes the existing Core
control surface over a localhost socket, so an external process can move stages,
change state, and run acquisitions by calling the SAME Core methods the GUI
buttons call.

- mesoSPIM_CommandServer.py (new): a QTimer-polled (non-blocking) TCP server
  speaking a small line-oriented JSON protocol. All Core-touching calls are
  isolated in one _CoreBridge class. Optional shared token gates access
  (fail-closed, constant-time compare over UTF-8 bytes); plain TCP, intended for
  a trusted LAN.
- mesoSPIM_Core: start_command_server(host, port, token) / stop_command_server()
  slots. Invoked via a queued connection so the server's socket/poll-timer live
  on the Core thread, where the Core's work runs (wait_until_done moves and
  acquisitions behave correctly).
- mesoSPIM_MainWindow: a "Tools -> Command Server..." menu entry (added
  programmatically, no .ui change) opening a small Start/Stop dialog with
  host/port/token and a token generator; stops the server on app close.

Nothing runs unless the operator starts it. Validated against -D demo mode: the
full connect -> get_config -> get_state -> move -> get_position -> acquire loop
runs against the real Core, including a real acquisition through the image
writer, with no hardware.
